On ''Brecha 5'', 3 km E of new highway from Santa Cruz to Camiri, the turnoff (''km 38'') 29 km S of junction with highway from Santa Cruz to Samaipata. Slightly rolling, sandy soil, mostly open soybean etc. fields of Mennonite colony to the east, still remnant forest to the west to the new highway from Santa Cruz to Camiri. Brushy divisions between fields with remnants of original semi-deciduous subtropical forest plus weekly forest plus weedy invaders such as Solanum riparium and Cnidoscolus basiacanthus.
